Maria Sevilla and her son Tyrone have had their visa application rejected because her son's autism would be a 'burden on the Australian health system' The single-mother and son will be deported back to the Philippines within 28 days . 
  Ms Sevilla has lived in Australia since 2007 and is a nurse in Townsville . 
  The Immigration Department said her son would be 'a significant cost to the Australian community' The Queensland government has called the decision 'cold and heartless' The mother and son initially had their application rejected due to Tyrone's autism . 
  She has had her appeal to the Immigration Department unsuccessful . 
  She and Tyrone will be forced out of the country within the next 28 days  . 
